defaultNotes.housingNotes:
Chaperone and Participant Sleeping Arrangements
For safety and supervision purposes, the following sleeping arrangements are mandatory:
Separation Requirements:
Chaperones and participants under 18 must maintain separate sleeping quarters at all times.

Knott Academic Center Arrangements:
   Chaperones assigned to participants housed in the Knott Academic Center shall sleep in designated areas outside the rooms occupied by their assigned participants.
   This arrangement ensures proper supervision while maintaining appropriate boundaries.

Gender-Specific Accommodations:
   Female chaperones will be provided with designated sleeping areas separate from participants.
   Adult participants (18 and over) will be housed in separate designated areas from minor participants.

Safety Protocol:
These arrangements are implemented to ensure a safe and appropriate environment for all participants and comply with youth protection guidelines.
defaultNotes.teenShowerPlan:
Female participants UNDER 18 may use the shower facilities in the lower concourse of the ARCC, including both the General Locker Rooms and Staff Locker Rooms.
Available times:
   Friday and Saturday nights: 10:00 PM - 12:00 AM
   Saturday and Sunday mornings: 5:30 AM - 7:30 AM

Male participants UNDER 18 may use the shower facilities in the Art Theater building.
Available times: Saturday and Sunday mornings: 5:30 AM - 7:30 AM
Transportation: ONLY ONE group will depart at 5:35 AM from the Knott Academic Center lobby
defaultNotes.adultShowerPlan:
Female participants OVER 18 may use the shower facilities in Locker Room 111 of the ARCC.
Available times:
   Friday and Saturday nights: 10:00 PM - 12:00 AM
   Saturday and Sunday mornings: 5:30 AM - 7:30 AM

Male participants OVER 18 may use the shower facilities one at a time in the Memorial Gym Locker Room or Farsatii Room.
Available times:
   Friday and Saturday nights: 10:00 PM - 12:00 AM
   Saturday and Sunday mornings: 5:30 AM - 7:30 AM
